The evidence with the title 'What are science & math test scores really telling U.S.? ' says Ago, U.S. fourth graders ranked twelfth in math and sixth in science among the students in 25 countries who took the test . By eighth grade, U.S. students had fallen to fifteenth in math and ninth in science among 45 nations measured . American students lagged behind such economic competitors as Singapore , Taiwan ,  ... 
